<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="544" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1487,2021]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1487,1512]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
First tergum brown; 
<number box="[510,523,1488,1512]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="2.0">2</number>
nd to 
<number box="[587,601,1488,1512]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="4.0">4</number>
th terga mostly yellow, with brown posterior margins; 
<number box="[1210,1222,1488,1512]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="5.0">5</number>
th to 
<number box="[1281,1294,1488,1512]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="7.0">7</number>
th terga dark brown; male genitalia uniformly yellow. Hypandrium broad, concave at base, apical part U-shaped, with a triangular projection medially; apical part with long dense hairs at posterior margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="546" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1487,2021]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,412,1595,1620]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544">Description. Male</emphasis>
. Body length 7.0 mm, wing length 
<quantity box="[810,899,1596,1620]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
. Head mostly yellow, except vertex black; hairs on head black. Compound eyes black without pubescence. Antenna with scape, pedicel and first flagellomere yellow, 
<number box="[245,258,1668,1692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="2.0">2</number>
nd to 
<number box="[331,357,1668,1692]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="13.0">13</number>
th flagellomeres dark brown, with uniformly black hairs. Proboscis yellow with black hairs. Palpus yellow, with black hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1487,2021]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544">
Thoracic dorsum mostly black, except middle part of scutellum yellow brown; mesopleuron uniformly yellow. Coxae and trochanters uniformly yellow; femora yellow at base, dark brown apically; tibiae mostly yellow, except apical margin dark brown; base of first tarsomere yellow, gradually darkened apically, 
<number box="[1135,1148,1812,1836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="2.0">2</number>
nd to 
<number box="[1214,1226,1812,1836]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="5.0">5</number>
th tarsomeres dark brown; hairs on legs black. Relative length of 
<number box="[666,676,1848,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="1.0">1</number>
st to 
<number box="[733,746,1848,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="5.0">5</number>
th tarsomeres in hindleg as 
<number box="[1053,1088,1848,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="9.2">9.2</number>
: 
<number box="[1109,1144,1848,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="2.1">2.1</number>
: 
<number box="[1165,1200,1848,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="1.3">1.3</number>
: 
<number box="[1221,1235,1848,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[1256,1271,1848,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="1.0">1</number>
. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[1361,1427,1848,1872]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 8" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[237,1319,209,1910]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1375,193,1949]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 8. Ptychoptera lii sp. nov. (male). 7. Habitus of male, lateral view; 8. Wing. Scale bar: 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221038/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="544">
Fig. 
<number box="[1413,1427,1848,1872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number box="[151,186,1884,1908]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="3.4">3.4</number>
times as long as wide, subhyaline. Wing marked with one narrow band and one brown cloud as follows: band extending from basal of Rs to middle section of CuA; brown cloud along basal part of R 
<number box="[1145,1153,1935,1949]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="4.0">4</number>
. Veins brown. Venation: Sc ending in C at level of basal 
<number box="[508,518,1959,1983]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[529,543,1959,1983]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="3.0">3</number>
of R 
<number box="[600,608,1974,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="2.0">2</number>
+ 
<number box="[617,624,1974,1988]" pageId="3" pageNumber="544" value="3.0">3</number>
; Rs shorter than r-m. Haltere yellow brown, with black hairs. Prehaltere yellow brown.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1260,1984,2007]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221038/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="545" targetBox="[237,1319,209,1910]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1260,1984,2007]" box="[151,1260,1984,2007]" pageId="4" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,1984,2007]" pageId="4" pageNumber="545">FIGURES 7–8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[320,471,1985,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii" status="sp. nov.">
