</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[478,558,1985,2006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="545" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[478,558,1985,2006]" pageId="4" pageNumber="545">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(male). 7. Habitus of male, lateral view; 8. Wing. Scale bar: 2.0 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221039/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" targetBox="[455,1131,193,1116]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1154,1207]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,326,1154,1177]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">FIGURES 9–12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[332,483,1155,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychoptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[332,483,1155,1177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">Ptychoptera lii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[489,569,1155,1176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[489,569,1155,1176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
9. Male Genitalia, lateral view; 10. Hypandrium, ventral view; 11. Epandrium, dorsal view; 12. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1252,1816]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">
Abdomen: First tergum brown; 
<number box="[556,569,1252,1276]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="2.0">2</number>
nd to 
<number box="[635,649,1252,1276]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="4.0">4</number>
th terga mostly yellow, with brown posterior margins; 
<number box="[1265,1278,1252,1276]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="5.0">5</number>
th to 
<number box="[1337,1350,1252,1276]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="7.0">7</number>
th terga dark brown; 
<number box="[296,306,1288,1312]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="1.0">1</number>
st to 
<number box="[366,380,1288,1312]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="4.0">4</number>
th sterna yellow, 
<number box="[576,589,1288,1312]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="5.0">5</number>
th to 
<number box="[649,661,1288,1312]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="8.0">8</number>
th sterna dark brown. Hairs on abdomen black. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1154,1177]" captionTargetBox="[455,1131,193,1116]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[439,1148,193,1133]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Ptychoptera lii sp. nov. 9. Male Genitalia, lateral view; 10. Hypandrium, ventral view; 11. Epandrium, dorsal view; 12. Gonocoxite and gonostylus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/221039/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">
Figs. 
<number box="[151,211,1324,1348]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12</number>
</figureCitation>
): Epandrium with a pair of posterior projections, each projection simple, broadest at base, tapering and incurve distally. Hypandrium broad at base, concave medially, apical part U-shaped, with a triangular projection medially, apical part with long dense hairs at posterior margin. Gonocoxite swollen ventrally. Gonostylus broad at base, medial part with a finger-like projection interiorly, truncate apically; distal part with a pair of branched projections, interior projection broad with short dense hairs, external projection narrow, finger-like. Paramere short, pointed apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1252,1816]" box="[199,418,1540,1565]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1541,1565]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
