<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="546" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1252,1816]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1720,1744]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Alexander" authorityName="Alexander" box="[776,1067,1720,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychaptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosensis">
<emphasis box="[776,940,1720,1744]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">P. formosensis</emphasis>
Alexander
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily separated from it by the wings being much wider and gonostylus with three projections. In 
<taxonomicName authority="Alexander" authorityName="Alexander" box="[1080,1384,1756,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Ptychopteridae" genus="Ptychaptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosensis">
<emphasis box="[1080,1252,1756,1780]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="546">P. formosensis</emphasis>
Alexander
</taxonomicName>
, the gonostylus is complex with five projections (
<bibRefCitation author="Nakamura" box="[654,964,1792,1816]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" refString="Nakamura, T. &amp; Saigusa, T. (2009) Taxonomic study of the family Ptychopteridae of Japan (Diptera). Zoosymposia, 3, 273 - 303." type="journal article" year="2009">
Nakamura &amp; Saigusa 
<number box="[903,964,1792,1816]" pageId="5" pageNumber="546" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
